### User:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Response:


This command sets up a secure shell (SSH) tunnel from the local machine to an Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) instance running on port 5900, allowing for remote access through port 25900. The "-i" option specifies the location of the private key file used for authentication and encryption, while "user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com" is the username to be authenticated with when connecting to the EC2 instance.
